From David Rind Subject Re centrifuge In article C JsM H efw Robert Feddeler MT T writes Could somebody explain to me what a centrifuge is and what it is used for I vaguely remembre it being something that spins test tubes around really fast but I cant remember why youd want to do that Purely recreational They get bored sitting in that rack all the time No, this is wrong The purpose is to preserve the substances in the tubes longer by creating relativistic speeds and thus time dilatation Of course, by slowing the subjective time of the test tubes they get less bored, which is probably what you were thinking of David Rind